spans.text: in languid note , While over the stream the dying echoes float
Let me , unruffled by your clamorous voice
the drear regions of the tomb my choice
Stalk over the gloomy grave , Muse ! be it thine To rouse the vain , the giddy , and supine , Who Pleasure's rounds pursue
the giddy , and supine , Who Pleasure's rounds
the harsh scream of yonder death-boding owl
thou wretched soul , OH teach a young , rash , inexperienced fool , What it's to die , and where thou wing'dst thy way

some darling friend , While strong convulsions their wild orbs extend ; One gasp , and deep eternity in view , The soul shoots forth , and groans a last adieu
no more — but O ! too curious maid
Then let me haste from this sad scene of woe
